text=This page provides a more complete list of some of the markup sequences available in PmWiki.  Note that it's easy to create and edit pages without using any of the markups below, but if you ever need them, they're here. ÀŠÀŠ(:comment To experiment with the rules, please try editing the Main/WikiSandbox. :)ÀŠÀŠãƒ«ãƒ¼ãƒ«ã®å®Ÿé¨“ã«ã¯ã€Main/WikiSandboxã‚’ç·¨é›†ã—ã¦ã¿ã¦ãã ã•ã„ã€‚ÀŠÀŠ----ÀŠ(:comment !!!Paragraphs :)ÀŠ!!!ãƒ‘ãƒ©ã‚°ãƒ©ãƒ•ÀŠÀŠ* Do not indent paragraphsÀŠ* Words wrap and fill as neededÀŠ* Use blank lines as separatorsÀŠ* Lines indented with one or more spaces (or tabs) are monospace font.ÀŠ* Use [@\@] (single backslash) at the end of a line to join the next line to the current one.ÀŠ* Use [@\\@] (two backslashes) at the end of a line to force a line break, but keep the current ''environment'' (e.g. stay inside the current list item).ÀŠÀŠ* ãƒ‘ãƒ©ã‚°ãƒ©ãƒ•ã¯ã‚¤ãƒ³ãƒ‡ãƒ³ãƒˆã—ã¾ã›ã‚“ã€‚ÀŠ* å¿…è¦ã«å¿œã˜ã¦ãƒ¯ãƒ¼ãƒ‰ãƒ©ãƒƒãƒ—ã¨ä¸­è©°ã‚ã‚’ã—ã¾ã™ã€‚ÀŠ* ã‚»ãƒ‘ãƒ¬ãƒ¼ã‚¿ã¨ã—ã¦ç©ºç™½è¡Œã‚’ä½¿ç”¨ã—ã¾ã™ã€‚ÀŠ* 1ã¤ä»¥ä¸Šã®ç©ºé–“æ–‡å­—(ã¾ãŸã¯ã€ã‚¿ãƒ–)ã§ã‚¤ãƒ³ãƒ‡ãƒ³ãƒˆã•ã‚ŒãŸè¡Œã¯ monospace font ã§ã™ã€‚ÀŠ* è¡Œæœ«ã«[@\@](ãƒãƒƒã‚¯ã‚¹ãƒ©ãƒƒã‚·ãƒ¥1ã¤)ã‚’ä½¿ã†ã¨ã€æ¬¡ã®è¡ŒãŒç¾åœ¨ã®è¡ŒãŒç¹‹ãŒã‚Šã¾ã™ã€‚ÀŠ* è¡Œæœ«ã«[@\\@](2ã¤ã®ãƒãƒƒã‚¯ã‚¹ãƒ©ãƒƒã‚·ãƒ¥)ã‚’ä½¿ã†ã¨å¼·åˆ¶æ”¹è¡Œã—ã¾ã™ã€‚ã—ã‹ã—ã€ç¾åœ¨ã®ã€Œç’°å¢ƒã€ãŒä¿ãŸã‚Œã¾ã™ã€‚(ä¾‹ãˆã°ã€ç¾åœ¨ã®ãƒªã‚¹ãƒˆé …ç›®ã®ä¸­ã«æ®‹ã‚Šã¾ã™)ã€‚ÀŠ----ÀŠ(:comment !!!Indented Paragraphs ''(Quotes)'' :)ÀŠ!!!ã‚¤ãƒ³ãƒ‡ãƒ³ãƒˆãƒ‘ãƒ©ã‚°ãƒ©ãƒ• ''(Quotes)''ÀŠÀŠArrows ([@->@]) at the beginning of a paragraph can be used to produce an indented paragraph.  More hyphens at the beginning ([@--->@]) produce larger indents.ÀŠÀŠ(:markup:) [=ÀŠ->Four score and seven years ago our fathers placed upon this continent a new nation, conceived in liberty and dedicated to the proposition that all men are created equal.ÀŠ=]ÀŠÀŠ----ÀŠ(:comment !!! [[#BulletedLists]] Bulleted Lists :)ÀŠ!!! [[#BulletedLists]] ç®‡æ¡æ›¸ãÀŠÀŠBullet lists are made by placing asterisks at the left margin.  More asterisks increases the level of bullet:ÀŠÀŠ(:markup:) [=ÀŠ* First-level list itemÀŠ** Second-level list itemÀŠ** Another second-level itemÀŠ* A first-level itemÀŠ=]ÀŠÀŠ----ÀŠ(:comment !!!Horizontal Line :)ÀŠ!!!æ°´å¹³ç·šÀŠÀŠFour or more dashes ([=----=]) at the beginning of a line produce a horizontal line.ÀŠÀŠ----ÀŠ(:comment !!!Emphasis :)ÀŠ!!!å¼·èª¿ÀŠÀŠ* Use doubled single-quotes ([=''=]), i.e., ''two apostrophes'', for emphasis (usually ''italics'')ÀŠ* Use tripled single-quotes ([='''=]), i.e. ''three apostrophes'', for strong emphasis (usually '''bold''')ÀŠ* Use five single-quotes ([='''''=]), or triples within doubles (''five apostrophes''), for some other kind of emphasis (usually '''''bold italics''''')ÀŠ* Use doubled at-signs ([=@@=]) for @@monospace@@ textÀŠ* Use [=[+...+]=] for [+larger text+] and [=[-...-]=] for [-smaller text-]ÀŠ* Emphasis can be used multiple times within a line, but cannot span across markup line boundaries (i.e., you can't put a paragraph break in the middle of bold text).ÀŠÀŠ(:comment Others styling :)ÀŠÀŠä»–ã®ã‚¹ã‚¿ã‚¤ãƒ«ÀŠ* [@'+big+', '-small-', '^super^', '_sub_', {+ins+}, {-del-}@].\\ÀŠ'+big+' , '-small-' , '^super^' , '_sub_' , {+ins+} , {-del-} ÀŠ* [@`WikiWord@] `WikiWord neutralisationÀŠÀŠÀŠSee also WikiStyles for advanced text formatting options.ÀŠÀŠ----ÀŠ(:comment !!!References :)ÀŠ!!!ãƒªãƒ•ã‚¡ãƒ¬ãƒ³ã‚¹ÀŠÀŠ* Use words and phrases in double brackets (e.g., [=[[text formatting rules]]=]) to create links to other pages on this wiki.ÀŠ* Capitalized words joined together (e.g., [[WikiWord]]s) can also be used to make references to other pages without needing the double-brackets.ÀŠ* Precede [=URLs=] with "http:", "ftp:", "gopher:", "mailto:", or "news:" to create links automatically, as in http://www.pmichaud.com/toast.ÀŠ* [=URLs=] ending with .gif, .jpg, or .png are displayed as images in the pageÀŠ* Links with arbitrary text can be created as either [=[[=]''target'' | ''text'']] or [=[[=]''text'' -> ''target''[=]]=].  ''Text'' can be an image URL, in which case the image becomes the link to the remote ''url'' or ''WikiWord''.ÀŠ* [[#Anchors]] Anchor targets within pages (#-links) can be created using @@[=[[#target]]=]@@.ÀŠÀŠ----ÀŠ(:comment !!!Headings :)ÀŠ!!!ãƒ˜ãƒƒãƒ€ÀŠÀŠHeadings are made by placing a exclamation mark ('''!''') at the left margin.  More exclamation marks increases the level of heading.  For example,ÀŠÀŠ(:markup:) [=ÀŠ! Level 1 HeadingÀŠ!! Level 2 HeadingÀŠ!!! Level 3 HeadingÀŠ!!!! Level 4 HeadingÀŠ=]ÀŠÀŠ----ÀŠ(:comment !!!Escape sequence :)ÀŠ!!!ã‚¨ã‚¹ã‚±ãƒ¼ãƒ—ã‚·ãƒ¼ã‚±ãƒ³ã‚¹ÀŠÀŠAnything placed between [=[= and =]=] is not interpreted by PmWiki/PmWiki.  This makes it possible to easily do [=WikiWords=] that are not links and turn off other special formatting interpretation.  The [=[= and =]=] can span multiple input lines, allowing effects to be applied to multiple input lines.  For example, space[[===] at the beginning of a line will cause the text up to the next =] to be monospace and uninterpreted by PmWiki/PmWiki (useful for program listings).ÀŠÀŠ----ÀŠ(:comment !!!Numbered Lists :)ÀŠ!!!æ•°å­—ãƒªã‚¹ãƒˆÀŠÀŠNumbered lists are made by placing number-signs (#) at the left margin.ÀŠÀŠ(:markup:) [=ÀŠ# Prepare the experimentÀŠ## Unwrap the pop-tartÀŠ## Insert the pop-tart into the toasterÀŠ# Begin cooking the pop tartÀŠ# Stand backÀŠ=]ÀŠÀŠ----ÀŠ(:comment !!! [[#DefinitionLists]] Definition Lists :)ÀŠ!!! [[#DefinitionLists]] å®šç¾©ãƒªã‚¹ãƒˆÀŠÀŠ(:comment Definition lists are made by placing colons at the left margin: :)ÀŠå®šç¾©ãƒªã‚¹ãƒˆã¯ã‚³ãƒ­ãƒ³ã‚’æ›¸ãã“ã¨ã§ãƒãƒ¼ã‚¸ãƒ³ã‚’ä½œã‚‹ã“ã¨ãŒå‡ºæ¥ã¾ã™:ÀŠÀŠ(:markup:) [=ÀŠ:term:definition of termÀŠ::second-level item: definition of 2nd-level itemÀŠ=]ÀŠÀŠ----ÀŠ(:comment !!!Tables :)ÀŠ!!!ãƒ†ãƒ¼ãƒ–ãƒ«ÀŠÀŠTable are defined by enclosing cells with '||'.  A cell with leading and trailing spaces is centered; a cell with leading spaces is right-aligned; all other cells are left-aligned.  An empty cell will cause the previous cell to span multiple columns.  (There is currently no mechanism for spanning multiple rows.)  A line beginning with '||' specifies the table attributes for subsequent tables. An '!' as the first character in a cell provides emphasis that can be used to provide headings.ÀŠÀŠ(:markup:) [=ÀŠ||align=center border=1 width=50%ÀŠ||!Table||!Heading||!Example||ÀŠ||!Left   || Center || Right||ÀŠ||A       ||!   B   ||     C||ÀŠ||        || single ||      ||ÀŠ||        || multi span   ||||ÀŠ=]ÀŠÀŠ----ÀŠ!!!ã“ã“ã§è¦‹ã¤ã‹ã‚‰ãªã‹ã£ãŸã‚‰ÀŠMarkupMasterIndex, [[ã‚·ãƒ³ãƒ—ãƒ«ãƒ†ãƒ¼ãƒ–ãƒ«]], [[ã‚·ãƒ³ãƒ—ãƒ«ãƒ†ãƒ¼ãƒ–ãƒ« 2]], [[æ‹¡å¼µãƒ†ãƒ¼ãƒ–ãƒ«]], [[ãƒªãƒ³ã‚¯]] ã‚’å‚ç…§ã—ã¦ãã ã•ã„ã€‚ÀŠÀŠ%trail%<<|[[PmWikiJa.ãƒ‰ã‚­ãƒ¥ãƒ¡ãƒ³ãƒˆç›®æ¬¡]]|>>
